FBIS3-47075 "dreas006_a_94019" FBIS-EAS-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Hearing on Political Reform Set for 17 Jan OW1001092494 Tokyo KYODO in English 0842 GMT 10 Jan 94 OW1001092494 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 10 KYODO -- The special committee on political reform of the House of Councillors voted Monday [10 January] to set a public hearing for government-proposed political reform bills for January 17. A bill can be put to the vote at a Diet committee after the public hearing is concluded. The four political reform bills that Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa has vowed to enact during the current Diet session, which ends January 29, are pending before the upper house after being passed by the House of Representatives in mid-November.
